WEBVTT

00:04:28.777 --> 00:04:30.491
On a good day, it's music,

00:04:30.515 --> 00:04:32.277
and I want to talk a little bit about

00:04:32.301 --> 00:04:36.416
the most amazing music-making
experience I ever had.

00:04:36.440 --> 00:04:39.632
I'm a farm boy. I grew
up surrounded by animals,

00:04:39.656 --> 00:04:41.631
and I would look in these eyes and wonder

00:04:41.655 --> 00:04:43.326
what was going on there?

00:04:43.350 --> 00:04:45.594
So as an adult, when
I started to read about

00:04:45.618 --> 00:04:48.863
the amazing breakthroughs
with Penny Patterson and Koko,

00:04:48.887 --> 00:04:52.097
with Sue Savage-Rumbaugh
and Kanzi, Panbanisha,

00:04:52.121 --> 00:04:54.518
Irene Pepperberg, Alex the parrot,

00:04:54.542 --> 00:04:56.986
I got all excited.

00:04:57.010 --> 00:04:58.957
What was amazing to me also

